Philip Holthouse Esq.


Holthouse, Carlin & Van Trigt LLP





                            Philip Holthouse serves as managing partner of Holthouse Carlin & Van Trigt LLP which he co-founded in 1991. HCVT has eight offices and over 350 employees in Southern California and Texas. He provides tax planning and tax consulting services for privately held businesses and high net-worth individuals primarily in the real estate, entertainment and service industries. He also consults on leasing and real estate transactions.Phil began his career with Peat Marwick & Mitchell (KPMG) in Los Angeles and worked as a tax manager in Peat Marwick’s national tax practice in Washington, D.C., where he monitored tax changes for the firm’s affiliate offices. He served as a part-time faculty member for USC’s Graduate Taxation Program for approximately ten years, and is a member of the Board of Advisors for the Leventhal School of Accounting at USC and the Graduate Tax Program at Loyola Law School. Other professional affiliations include the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the California Society of Certified Public Accountants, the American Bar Association, and the State Bar of California. Phil also serves on the boards of Ascent Capital Group (NASDAQ) and several non-profit organizations including Harvard-Westlake School, the Music Center Leadership Council, and the Angeleno and Los Angeles chapters of WPO.Education:J.D., Loyola Law School in Los AngelesM.S., Business Taxation, University of Southern California summa cum laudeB.S., Business Administration, University of Southern California summa cum laudeBloomberg BNA Tax Management Portfolios:593 T.M., Real Estate Leases (co-author)













