Executive Profile
Philip J. Holthouse  Managing Partner, Holthouse Carlin & Van Trigt LLPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. Philip J. Holthouse, also known as Phil, co-founded Holthouse Carlin & Van Trigt LLP in 1991 and has been its Managing Partner/Partner since 1991. Mr. Holthouse began his career at Peat Marwick & Mitchell (now KPMG) in Los Angeles and served as a Tax Manager in its National Tax Practice in Washington, D.C., where he monitored tax changes for its affiliate offices. He has been an Independent Director at Ascent Capital Group, Inc. since September 2008. Mr. Holthouse ... served as a Director of Napster Inc. (formerly, Roxio Inc.) from January 8, 2004 to October 30, 2008. He is the Chairman of the Board of Advisors for the Leventhal School of Accounting at USC. He is a Member of the Board of Advisors for the Graduate Tax Program at Loyola Law School. He serves on the boards of several non-profit organizations including The Curtis School, Harvard-Westlake School and Young President' Organization, Los Angeles Chapter. Other professional affiliations include the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the California Society of Certified Public Accountants, the American Bar Association and the State Bar of California. He was a Part-time Faculty Member for USC's Graduate Taxation Program. He frequently authors articles on taxation and has been featured on NBC Nightly News and Financial News Network as a Tax Specialist. He is a Certified Public Accountant. A summa cum laude graduate, Mr. Holthouse holds a Master's Degree in Business Taxation and a Bachelor's Degree in Business Administration, both from the University of Southern California and a Law Degree from Loyola Law School in Los Angeles.Read Full Background




